"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The shape of the descending part of the T wave can effect the measurement of the QT interval when using the tangent method. The two hypothetical T waves have the same offset time (vertical solid line). However, the two T waves have a significantly different shape of the descending part; as a result, a tangent to the steepest point may significantly underestimate (top panel, red dash line) or overestimate the T wave offset (bottom panel, black dash line).",
